SIMPLE: deadening
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: deadening
<hw>dead"en*ing</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <ety>[<pos>p. pr.</pos> of verb
<er>deaden</er>{3}.]</ety> <def>Rendering less lively, intense, or
vigorous; <as>as, the <ex>deadening</ex> effect of some routine
tasks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>So lacking in interest as to cause mental weariness;
<as>as, the <ex>deadening</ex> effect of some routine
tasks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> boring, dreary, ho-hum, irksome, tedious, tiresome,
wearisome.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>deadening</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: deadening
<hw>dead"en*ing</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of making something
futile and useless (as by routine).</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> stultification, impairment.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dead-eye</ent>⟦br⟧
